WEBVTT

00:02.298 --> 00:03.925
Racing's a man's game.

00:03.999 --> 00:05.364
Can't you win
in a fair race?

00:05.434 --> 00:06.492
[groaning]

00:07.136 --> 00:09.036
Hi, Kid.
lt's nice to see you,
Uncle John.

00:09.204 --> 00:10.899
l mean,
that Kyle Ludwig is crazy.

00:10.973 --> 00:12.338
He almost killed
Dana and the baby...

00:12.408 --> 00:14.205
trashed my car
and put me in here.

00:15.344 --> 00:17.039
That ought to get
his engine started.

00:17.112 --> 00:19.046
Looks like Decker's got
a surprise party for us.

00:19.114 --> 00:20.843
(Murdock)
So if you're looking
for the A-Team...

00:20.916 --> 00:21.883
you're out of luck.

00:21.951 --> 00:22.975
You're dead.

00:24.553 --> 00:26.714
The only place you're going
is to prison, Smith.

00:26.789 --> 00:28.416
How are you today?

00:28.724 --> 00:30.055
(Decker)
There they go!

00:30.359 --> 00:31.951
Get ready for
the main event.

00:34.029 --> 00:36.327
(male narrator)
In 1972,
a crack commando unit....

00:36.398 --> 00:38.298
was sent to prison
by a military court....

00:38.367 --> 00:39.698
for a crime
they didn't commit.

00:39.768 --> 00:41.030
These men promptly escaped...

00:41.136 --> 00:42.660
from a maximum-security
stockade....

00:42.738 --> 00:44.296
to the Los Angeles
underground.

00:44.406 --> 00:46.033
Today, still wanted
by the government....

00:46.108 --> 00:48.076
they survive
as soldiers of fortune.

00:48.143 --> 00:50.703
If you have a problem,
if no one else can help...

00:50.779 --> 00:52.007
and if you can find them...

00:52.081 --> 00:54.015
maybe you can hire
the A-Team.

00:54.116 --> 00:55.811
[gun firing]

00:57.000 --> 01:03.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

02:17.533 --> 02:18.864
(Jack)
l think it's okay, honey...

02:18.934 --> 02:21.061
if you give it
a little gas along here.

02:21.537 --> 02:23.437
That way
we'll make up some time.

02:23.939 --> 02:26.430
You sound just like
your son, you know that?

02:26.508 --> 02:29.136
That's all you two
think about,
is driving faster.

02:29.812 --> 02:33.976
l promised my boy l'd get you
to the doctor's appointment
on time, didn't l?

02:34.049 --> 02:37.450
l mean, he must've made me
promise at least
a half a dozen times.

02:37.519 --> 02:40.283
l swear, l don't know
who's more nervous
about having this baby...

02:40.355 --> 02:41.344
him or me.

02:41.423 --> 02:42.856
Besides, it only
an appointment.

02:42.925 --> 02:45.155
l'll probably have to sit
in the waiting room anyway.

02:46.095 --> 02:48.359
And l won't tell him
that you overslept.

02:48.430 --> 02:50.694
Honey, you are
the greatest.

02:52.701 --> 02:54.692
Well, look at that.

02:55.037 --> 02:57.631
Jack Harmon must be
going someplace
in a real hurry.

02:57.773 --> 02:58.865
He ought to be
more careful.

02:58.941 --> 03:00.932
He could have
a real bad accident
driving that fast.

03:01.610 --> 03:03.305
[tires squealing]

03:06.815 --> 03:09.079
You know sometimes
l just can't believe it...

03:09.151 --> 03:11.779
that you and the Kid
are gonna have a baby.

03:12.488 --> 03:14.615
And l'm gonna have me
a grandson.

03:14.690 --> 03:15.884
Or a granddaughter.

03:15.958 --> 03:19.416
Maybe we'll hit the jackpot
and we'll have one of each.

03:20.195 --> 03:21.492
[Jack chuckling]

04:06.575 --> 04:08.440
Don't you think
you've had enough
to drink?

04:08.777 --> 04:10.802
They ran us
off the road, son.

04:10.879 --> 04:12.403
There wasn't anything
l could do.

04:12.481 --> 04:14.176
Oh, man, you should've
done something.

04:14.249 --> 04:15.580
You were supposed
to be driving.

04:15.651 --> 04:16.913
That's what
you were there for.

04:16.985 --> 04:19.351
You know, if you'd
just called Uncle John
in the first place...

04:19.421 --> 04:20.786
this whole thing
never would have happened.

04:20.856 --> 04:23.017
Uncle John. Don't tell me
about Uncle John.

04:23.292 --> 04:26.261
He's no better than
Kyle Ludwig and the rest
of his goons.

04:26.395 --> 04:28.920
l'm sure not
gonna be forced out
of this championship.

04:28.997 --> 04:31.465
Maybe it's time somebody
did something about it.

04:31.967 --> 04:33.832
Hey, Kid! Kid, don't!

04:34.770 --> 04:35.862
Kid!

04:47.950 --> 04:48.974
Ludwig!

04:49.051 --> 04:50.450
l wanna talk
to you, now!

04:51.820 --> 04:54.846
Well, if it's not
the famous Kid Harmon.

04:55.424 --> 04:57.051
How you doing, Kid?

04:57.125 --> 04:58.490
Oh, how's the family, huh?

04:59.995 --> 05:02.020
You're all through
harassing me and my wife.

05:02.097 --> 05:03.223
No kidding.

05:03.298 --> 05:04.856
Yeah, no kidding, man.

05:06.134 --> 05:10.662
You listen to me.
You see, racing....
Racing's a man's game.

05:11.039 --> 05:14.167
And one of these days,
when you grow up,
maybe you'll qualify, huh?

05:14.276 --> 05:15.607
[groaning]

05:17.579 --> 05:18.671
[panting]
Listen, man.

05:18.747 --> 05:21.147
Nothing's gonna make me
drop out of the championship.

05:21.216 --> 05:22.342
Nothing, Ludwig.

05:22.417 --> 05:26.478
You know, l ask myself,
l say, how come this kid
is such a slow learner, huh?

05:26.855 --> 05:29.221
l mean, how come
all the other drivers
on this track...

05:29.291 --> 05:31.759
understand that l'm gonna
win the title, not you?

05:31.827 --> 05:33.226
No, not you.

05:33.795 --> 05:36.229
l mean, even your own pit crew
got the hint.

05:36.298 --> 05:37.822
They took off
early this morning.

05:37.899 --> 05:39.560
Can't you win
in a fair race?

05:40.669 --> 05:45.299
Well, let's just say
that l truly hate losers...

05:45.974 --> 05:48.101
and these boys here,
they're gonna show you...

05:48.176 --> 05:50.167
the kind of loser
you really are.

05:55.350 --> 05:58.842
Oops. Looks like you got
car trouble, Kid, huh?

06:01.657 --> 06:02.783
[groaning]

06:06.228 --> 06:07.991
You take Kid Harmon...

06:08.730 --> 06:11.221
and you take him
out of the lineup
permanently.

06:13.268 --> 06:15.259
You'll have to leave soon.
We need the room.

06:15.337 --> 06:16.827
l'll prepare
the discharge papers.

06:16.905 --> 06:17.929
Hi, Kid.

06:18.006 --> 06:19.701
Uncle John,
what are you doing here?

06:19.775 --> 06:22.403
So good to see you,
Uncle John.
Thank you for coming.

06:22.477 --> 06:25.446
Well, sure. l was here
for the Boy Scout jamboree,
wasn't l?

06:25.514 --> 06:26.811
This is no jamboree
this time.

06:27.049 --> 06:29.517
Yeah, we know.
Dana told us all about it
when she called.

06:29.584 --> 06:31.211
You shouldn't have
done that, Dana.

06:31.286 --> 06:33.049
There's nothing anybody
can do for me.

06:33.121 --> 06:34.520
Kyle Ludwig
has seen to that.

06:34.589 --> 06:37.387
l remember when the military
thought they could keep us
from your wedding.

06:37.459 --> 06:39.154
And a lovely wedding
it was, too.

06:39.227 --> 06:41.422
You know, l kept a piece
of your wedding cake...

06:41.496 --> 06:43.157
and l put in the back
of B.A.'s van...

06:43.231 --> 06:45.222
and it got all moldy
and started to spread wings.

06:45.300 --> 06:46.733
You left cake
in my van?

06:47.436 --> 06:51.634
Don't give up, honey.
Uncle John took a big risk
coming here like this.

06:51.707 --> 06:54.574
You know
how that Colonel Decker
is always snooping around.

06:54.643 --> 06:56.611
l never knew you
to be a quitter, Kid.

06:56.778 --> 06:59.713
What did you expect me to do?
l mean, that Kyle Ludwig
is crazy.

06:59.781 --> 07:01.339
He almost killed
Dana and the baby...

07:01.416 --> 07:03.350
trashed my car
and put me in here.

07:04.252 --> 07:07.016
Face, maybe you could check
on that bill with that nurse.

07:07.089 --> 07:08.078
All right.

07:08.657 --> 07:11.558
We gotta get that cake
out of my van. Come on.

07:14.329 --> 07:15.421
You know, Kid...

07:15.797 --> 07:18.265
B.A.'s got his heart set
on fixing your car.

07:18.433 --> 07:20.993
There's not a store
in the county
that'll sell him spare parts.

07:21.069 --> 07:22.468
Kyle Ludwig has seen
to that.

07:22.537 --> 07:24.664
Well, Dana said your father
was getting us parts.

07:24.740 --> 07:25.900
My father's what?

07:26.074 --> 07:27.974
He wanted to
make it up to you, honey.

07:28.043 --> 07:29.670
He felt bad
about what happened.

07:29.745 --> 07:31.372
l guess things
aren't any better
with Jack, huh?

07:31.646 --> 07:32.670
Better?

07:32.748 --> 07:34.477
His drinking's gotten
worse than ever.

07:35.050 --> 07:36.449
lf he did go for parts...

07:36.518 --> 07:38.611
he'd have to go
to some other county,
is that right?

07:38.687 --> 07:40.314
Right.
Well, where'd he go?

07:40.389 --> 07:41.856
He took 1 24 to Trenton.

07:42.224 --> 07:44.249
Check out of here,
we'll meet you
at the garage.

07:44.326 --> 07:45.315
Okay.

07:45.394 --> 07:47.328
Do you think Ludwig
would try to stop him?

07:48.029 --> 07:49.121
We'll find out.

07:50.966 --> 07:52.160
[sighs]

07:57.506 --> 08:00.907
Looks like
Mr. Ludwig was right
about old Jack Harmon.

08:01.676 --> 08:04.941
He's going for spare parts
to rebuild the Kid's car
for the race.

08:05.013 --> 08:07.538
Some insurance company
sure ain't gonna be
too happy about...

08:07.616 --> 08:09.277
all the accidents
this family's having.

08:44.986 --> 08:46.613
l think we're too late,
Colonel.

08:46.688 --> 08:48.155
Let's go get them, B.A.

08:52.761 --> 08:54.388
[tires squealing]

09:41.076 --> 09:42.270
Jack, you
all right?

09:42.577 --> 09:45.273
l was just fine
till you showed up.

09:56.625 --> 09:59.719
lt's like l told you,
Uncle John. l mean,
lt's a total loss.

10:00.295 --> 10:03.321
Kyle Ludwig is gonna be
running this race alone now.

10:03.398 --> 10:05.332
Now, this mess
is beyond fixing.

10:05.400 --> 10:07.493
Hey, Kid, if it's got
a engine in it...

10:07.569 --> 10:08.934
B.A. Baracus
can fix it.

10:09.004 --> 10:10.369
Why are you
reacting like that?

10:10.438 --> 10:12.599
Kid here, he didn't mean
no offense by what he said.

10:12.674 --> 10:16.701
He just doesn't realize
that you are a consummate
internal-combustion artist...

10:16.778 --> 10:20.612
born with a socket wrench
in one hand and 10W40
coursing through your veins.

10:20.682 --> 10:23.810
You know our B.A. here,
his first job was a lube job.

10:23.885 --> 10:25.750
lf you don't shut up
with your jibber-jabber...

10:25.820 --> 10:27.651
l'm gonna give you
a lube job, fool.

10:29.457 --> 10:32.790
Well, l checked out
Kyle Ludwig, all right...

10:32.861 --> 10:35.159
and, oh, l just want to know,
we haven't lost our knack...

10:35.230 --> 10:38.791
for putting ourselves
in the most dangerous
situations possible.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.594
Man, l told you.
Kyle Ludwig won't let
anybody get near him.

10:41.670 --> 10:43.934
Yeah, kind of makes you wonder
how a guy like that...

10:44.005 --> 10:47.168
can pay for a racecar,
pit crew...

10:47.309 --> 10:49.641
and, oh, the bodyguards
with 40-inch necks.

10:49.711 --> 10:53.704
He gets his money
the old-fashioned way.
He earns it.

10:53.815 --> 10:55.214
No, Murdock, no.

10:55.283 --> 10:58.650
l think he does
what a lot of young people
do these days.

10:58.720 --> 11:00.085
He gets money
from home.

11:00.155 --> 11:03.283
Unfortunately for us,
''home'' in this case
happens to be...

11:03.358 --> 11:06.521
a Chicago crime family
run by his dear uncle.

11:06.661 --> 11:09.824
Uncle Carl
''The Hatchet'' Ludwig.

11:10.198 --> 11:13.395
Whatever Kyle wants,
his dear Uncle Carl
gives him?

11:13.468 --> 11:14.799
l hear they're very close.

11:15.236 --> 11:16.965
l had an Uncle Carl once.

11:17.372 --> 11:18.737
He was a milkman.

11:18.807 --> 11:21.708
But l never got
anything out of him
but cottage cheese.

11:21.776 --> 11:24.404
Oh, fool, your brain's
made of cottage cheese.

11:24.479 --> 11:25.571
Honey.

11:26.648 --> 11:28.115
lt'll be all right, Dana.

11:29.517 --> 11:31.212
Uncle John will know
what to do.

11:31.353 --> 11:32.877
Murdock,
you got first watch.

11:32.954 --> 11:36.720
When Kyle finds out
what we did to his musclemen,
we won't be very popular.

11:36.791 --> 11:38.019
Hmm, no.

11:39.260 --> 11:41.820
No, if he'd just
take the time
to get to know us.

11:41.896 --> 11:44.922
Uncle John,
do you really think
Ludwig would come here...

11:45.000 --> 11:47.560
l mean, to our own garage,
in the middle of the day?

11:47.636 --> 11:49.797
Never put a stupid move
past a stupid man.

11:49.871 --> 11:51.429
lt's a rule
of survival, Dana.

11:51.506 --> 11:53.736
Here we have another
pearl of wisdom...

11:53.808 --> 11:56.504
according to the great
Saint Smith, huh?

11:56.845 --> 11:59.473
All the while l thought
you were a friend
of the family's.

11:59.547 --> 12:00.741
l can't really believe...

12:00.815 --> 12:03.249
that you're gonna put my kids
in the middle of a war.

12:03.585 --> 12:06.281
Now, we wouldn't want Ludwig
to think he won, would we?

12:06.354 --> 12:08.549
This old wreck
is not gonna run
and you know it.

12:08.623 --> 12:12.115
Hey, if you think that,
then why did you even bother
trying to get parts?

12:12.193 --> 12:13.854
Listen to me, son.

12:13.928 --> 12:15.919
He can make all the promises
he wants to...

12:15.997 --> 12:17.589
but he can't drive
the race for you.

12:17.666 --> 12:19.327
What the kid needs
is a new car.

12:19.401 --> 12:22.859
Now, there's one guy
that l know
who's got enough money...

12:22.937 --> 12:25.531
to buy that new car,
and that's Ludwig himself.

12:25.607 --> 12:29.134
But why would Kyle Ludwig
give us money for a car?

12:29.244 --> 12:31.838
Oh, l'm sure he'll be
extremely generous...

12:31.913 --> 12:33.938
if Face asks him
the right way.

12:34.582 --> 12:35.606
Yeah.

12:36.851 --> 12:38.910
(Ludwig)
How much time do you need,
anyhow, huh?

12:38.987 --> 12:40.614
l send you out to do
a simple little job...

12:40.689 --> 12:42.953
you come back here
with your tails
between your legs.

12:43.491 --> 12:46.187
Harmons must've hired
some heavy hitters,
Mr. Ludwig.

12:46.261 --> 12:48.855
Oh, is that what you want me
to tell my Uncle Carl, huh?

12:48.930 --> 12:52.366
You are supposed
to be the heavy hitters
from Chicago, remember?

12:52.434 --> 12:54.902
We'll make sure Kid Harmon
doesn't rebuild his car,
don't worry.

12:54.969 --> 12:56.459
Oh, no, l'm not
gonna worry, huh?

12:56.538 --> 12:58.438
Harmon's the only driver
on the whole circuit...

12:58.506 --> 13:00.440
that could take
the championship
away from me...

13:00.508 --> 13:02.772
and l tell you,
if he gets one wheel
on that track...

13:02.844 --> 13:06.109
my Uncle Carl's gonna know
just how unhappy l am.
You understand me?

13:06.347 --> 13:07.371
[phone ringing]

13:07.449 --> 13:09.417
Get it, on your way out.

13:09.751 --> 13:12.413
l'm gonna give these girls
a chance to relax me.

13:13.054 --> 13:14.180
l'm so tense.

13:14.956 --> 13:17.186
[phone continues ringing]

13:17.525 --> 13:18.651
Yeah?

13:19.494 --> 13:21.621
Mr. Ludwig don't wanna
see anybody right now.

13:23.898 --> 13:25.456
The Figoratti racing team?

13:25.800 --> 13:27.563
Figoratti?
What about Figoratti?

13:27.635 --> 13:30.297
Some guy outside. He says
he's supposed to have
an appointment with you.

13:30.371 --> 13:32.066
He's with the Figoratti
racing team from ltaly.

13:32.140 --> 13:34.233
l know where
the Figoratti team is.

13:34.309 --> 13:36.334
They're the best
in the world.
Send the guy in.

13:36.411 --> 13:37.503
Come in.

13:38.480 --> 13:39.538
Stupid.

13:41.816 --> 13:43.215
There you go.

13:44.319 --> 13:45.445
Here.

13:46.454 --> 13:47.443
[sighing]

13:48.323 --> 13:49.790
Here you are.

13:50.191 --> 13:51.249
Dave Pacini...

13:51.326 --> 13:53.726
Figoratti Racing
representative
for the Western Hemisphere.

13:54.796 --> 13:58.892
Let me compliment you,
Mr. Ludwig, on your
excellent staff.

13:58.967 --> 14:00.298
Your associate
in the hallway...

14:00.368 --> 14:03.565
he questioned me
most thoroughly
about why l'm here.

14:03.638 --> 14:04.866
So, why are you here?

14:04.939 --> 14:06.531
Well, it was all
in my letter. You....

14:08.309 --> 14:10.834
Oh, no. Don't tell me. You....

14:11.312 --> 14:12.870
You see, my secretary
in New York...

14:12.947 --> 14:14.938
she assured me
all the arrangements
had been made.

14:15.016 --> 14:17.712
Then l show up here.
l don't even have
hotel reservations.

14:17.786 --> 14:20.653
l should have anticipated
it was gonna be
one of these days, huh?

14:21.022 --> 14:23.354
You never got my letter,
am l right?

14:23.424 --> 14:24.652
You're right.

14:24.726 --> 14:26.159
Let me be brief.
Please.

14:26.261 --> 14:30.630
Okay. The Figoratti family,
as you well know,
has proudly financed...

14:30.698 --> 14:33.861
five racing teams
on the international
circuit...

14:33.935 --> 14:35.835
for, well,
for many years.

14:35.904 --> 14:40.603
Unfortunately, recent
mounting costs have made it
necessary for them to seek...

14:41.009 --> 14:44.672
oh, how shall we put it,
outside revenue sources.

14:44.746 --> 14:46.771
You know, everybody knows
in the racing world...

14:46.848 --> 14:49.976
this Figoratti guy's
a playboy and he's blowing
the family fortune, right?

14:50.051 --> 14:52.611
So why don't you just
cut through the grease job
here, all right?

14:52.720 --> 14:53.709
[titters]

14:54.522 --> 14:55.682
[hesitantly]
Can....

14:55.757 --> 14:57.987
Can we discuss this
in private?

14:58.393 --> 15:00.827
Oh, absolutely.
Take a hike.

15:01.529 --> 15:04.555
But the girls stay.
They know better
than to talk, don't you?

15:04.632 --> 15:05.963
[laughing]

15:06.534 --> 15:08.627
Great country, isn't it?
Certainly is.

15:10.271 --> 15:13.069
Well, let me be candid,
Mr. Ludwig.

15:13.274 --> 15:16.835
Giancarlo Figoratti
can no longer afford
the millions it takes...

15:16.911 --> 15:18.970
to keep five teams
in operation.

15:19.047 --> 15:20.071
What's in it for me?

15:20.148 --> 15:22.139
Tell me, have you ever...

15:22.217 --> 15:25.311
given any consideration
to driving international
Formula 1?

15:25.386 --> 15:26.478
Formula 1?

15:26.688 --> 15:30.283
Are you telling me
that l could buy my way onto
the Figoratti racing team?

15:31.125 --> 15:33.650
Formula 1, huh?
l mean, of course
l want to drive one.

15:33.728 --> 15:36.094
God, l'd blow
the whole field away
with a Formula 1 .

15:36.164 --> 15:37.791
Well, how much dough
are we talking about?

15:37.866 --> 15:40.926
Oh, million dollars.
Spread over the whole season.

15:41.536 --> 15:43.163
Million dollars.
Yes.

15:43.338 --> 15:47.206
Now, what makes you think
l got that kind of money, huh?

15:47.408 --> 15:50.002
Mr. Ludwig, you come
from a very wealthy...

15:50.078 --> 15:52.046
very influential family.

15:52.513 --> 15:55.607
And word has it
that there may be certain...

15:55.850 --> 15:59.877
profits that need
to be disposed of
in quiet European ventures.

15:59.954 --> 16:02.047
l'll tell you what,
l've decided to like you.

16:02.123 --> 16:03.886
You call me Kyle
from now on, all right?

16:03.958 --> 16:06.017
And l'll talk
to my Uncle Carl
about the money.

16:06.094 --> 16:07.186
Excellent.

16:07.262 --> 16:09.560
Well, l have to talk
to some other
potential investors...

16:09.631 --> 16:11.622
so what say
we connect in, oh....

16:11.699 --> 16:14.600
