34:06.340 --> 34:09.070
The only place you're going
is to prison, Smith.

34:09.141 --> 34:11.110
Decker, what a surprise.
l'll bet it is.

34:11.178 --> 34:12.167
(Crane)
Good work, Harmon.

34:12.411 --> 34:14.880
l knew
all those wanted posters
l distributed on you...

34:14.947 --> 34:17.246
had to pay off
sooner or later, Smith.

34:17.317 --> 34:20.753
l just never dreamed
it would be one your friends
who'd turn you in.

34:22.856 --> 34:25.347
[imitating ltalian accent]
Slowly. Slowly.

34:37.270 --> 34:39.135
Go! Go! Go! Go!

34:44.444 --> 34:46.071
l don't understand
why he's late, Dana.

34:46.146 --> 34:47.408
He should be here by now.

34:47.481 --> 34:48.846
Why would Uncle John
stand me up?

34:48.915 --> 34:52.783
He'll be here, honey.
You know how he's on the run.
He's got to be careful.

34:52.853 --> 34:54.547
Yeah, but the race
is about to begin.

34:54.621 --> 34:56.782
l can't drive without B.A.
and Uncle John.

34:56.857 --> 34:58.449
Damn it!
They let me down.

34:58.525 --> 35:01.619
That not true, son.
l'm the one
that let you down.

35:01.695 --> 35:03.356
You're here, Dad.

35:03.964 --> 35:05.795
After all those things
l said about you...

35:05.866 --> 35:07.527
l'm surprised
you even bothered.

35:07.934 --> 35:10.926
(announcer on PA)
Attention, gentlemen,
the five-minute board is up.

35:11.505 --> 35:13.268
The car is running fine.

35:13.373 --> 35:15.967
You give the spectators
a whopping show. Hmm?

35:16.109 --> 35:17.269
We'll talk later.

35:17.344 --> 35:18.368
Good luck.

35:18.445 --> 35:19.776
All right.

35:20.213 --> 35:21.544
Do me luck.
Here goes nothing!

35:26.753 --> 35:28.550
[car engine revving]

35:32.926 --> 35:33.893
Go get them.

35:43.770 --> 35:44.794
[engine starting]

35:44.871 --> 35:46.532
That's Kid Harmon
in number 4.

35:46.606 --> 35:47.971
You know
what we gotta do.

35:48.041 --> 35:49.372
Make him
part of the wall.

35:49.443 --> 35:50.671
He's a short runner.

35:59.786 --> 36:01.310
All right, men.

36:01.655 --> 36:05.819
We know from Jack Harmon
the A-Team's been working
with a fourth man.

36:06.460 --> 36:09.361
So, be ready
for an attempt to rescue
Smith and the others.

36:09.629 --> 36:10.755
Roger, Colonel.

36:18.605 --> 36:20.766
(Murdock)
Mamma mia.

36:21.708 --> 36:25.439
[chattering ltalian-sounding
gibberish]

36:25.579 --> 36:27.843
[in ltalian]

36:27.914 --> 36:30.109
What is this guy
trying to tell us?
Beats me.

36:30.183 --> 36:33.744
Hey, what are you
trying to tell us?

36:34.955 --> 36:38.152
[articulating]
Why did you bring us here?

36:38.225 --> 36:39.487
[stammering]

36:39.559 --> 36:41.356
Carl Ludwig....

36:42.529 --> 36:44.053
How you say?

36:44.965 --> 36:46.830
He's got a problem....

36:48.568 --> 36:51.366
Famiglia, famiglia fighting.

36:51.438 --> 36:52.928
Famiglia what?
Who's fighting?

36:53.006 --> 36:55.839
His family's fighting.
Somebody's fighting
with his family!

36:55.909 --> 36:58.036
Carl Ludwig...

36:59.880 --> 37:03.372
he's no good friends
with Al Capone. Capisce?

37:03.450 --> 37:04.781
Al Capone?

37:05.218 --> 37:07.311
l think he means
it a hit on the Ludwigs.

37:07.687 --> 37:11.987
Hey, maybe somebody's trying
to get to Carl ''The Hatchet''
by making a move on Kyle.

37:12.058 --> 37:14.492
Pretending to be
the military.
lt's a good cover.

37:15.262 --> 37:16.695
Carl wants to do
something about this.

37:16.997 --> 37:21.366
[in ltalian]

37:21.434 --> 37:25.029
Thanks, Mr. Figoratti.
We'll take care of this,
don't worry.

37:25.105 --> 37:28.074
Hello. How are you today?
Thank you very much. Okay?

37:28.241 --> 37:30.573
Hello. Thank you
very much, okay?

37:31.311 --> 37:32.300
Come on.

37:50.130 --> 37:51.995
Don't move.
Not one of you.

37:53.066 --> 37:56.058
The A-Team accomplices
are making their move.
Roll them out.

37:57.571 --> 38:00.438
(Face and Hannibal)
[ You are my sunshine [

38:00.507 --> 38:03.476
[ My only sunshine [

38:03.543 --> 38:06.376
[ You make me happy [[

38:06.446 --> 38:08.710
[bell clanging]
[ Oh, l found a cow [

38:08.848 --> 38:10.713
[mooing]
[ Under my shoe [

38:10.850 --> 38:14.013
[ l found a cow,
how about you? [

38:14.955 --> 38:16.582
[ l found a cow [[

38:16.957 --> 38:19.425
[[[scatting]

38:19.626 --> 38:20.854
[mooing]

38:21.027 --> 38:22.221
Come on, girl.

38:22.295 --> 38:24.422
Come on, right here,
right here. Come on.

38:24.497 --> 38:26.465
Yeah. Take it easy.
There you go.

38:26.533 --> 38:29.297
Take it easy, Bessie.
Take it easy.

38:30.604 --> 38:33.903
Think of
how your milk's gonna make
all those boys and girls...

38:33.974 --> 38:37.774
nice and healthy and strong,
and just think of how proud
B.A. is going to be of you.

38:40.947 --> 38:43.973
God, this is a terrible road.
Why'd we have to come
this way?

38:44.751 --> 38:47.345
lt's the only other way
back to the interstate.

38:47.554 --> 38:49.021
(soldier #1)
What's this?

38:51.958 --> 38:53.425
[[[singing]

38:59.766 --> 39:02.963
Hey, Pops, you wanna
do that someplace else?
We're in a hurry here.

39:03.403 --> 39:05.132
Hey, you from the city, boy?

39:05.205 --> 39:07.196
Well, yeah
What's that got to do
with moving the cow?

39:07.274 --> 39:11.074
Well, l thought as much,
'cause lf you spent
any time on a farm...

39:11.144 --> 39:15.444
you'd know that
when a lady like Bessie here
wants to give milk...

39:15.515 --> 39:17.676
[laughing]
she gives milk.

39:19.753 --> 39:21.482
Aw, take
a little bit more.

39:21.588 --> 39:22.577
Yeah.

39:24.524 --> 39:26.287
Hey, Hank, you wanna
give us a hand here?

39:26.359 --> 39:27.587
Yeah! Hey, Hank!

39:27.661 --> 39:30.027
Hey, Hank, come on down here
and give us a hand.

39:30.096 --> 39:31.688
'Cause they ain't
gonna be no good.

39:31.765 --> 39:33.596
You gonna need more hands
than you got, boy.

39:33.667 --> 39:35.328
Here, let me take that
for you.

39:35.935 --> 39:36.959
[cow mooing]

39:37.037 --> 39:38.299
(Murdock)
Yeah.

39:38.371 --> 39:39.702
Keep on pushing.

39:39.773 --> 39:41.707
As my daddy sang
in that old song....

39:41.775 --> 39:43.436
[ Keep on pushing [[

39:43.843 --> 39:45.333
Keep on pushing, boys.

39:52.986 --> 39:54.419
Let's go.

40:09.135 --> 40:10.329
Good afternoon, gentlemen.

40:10.403 --> 40:13.270
This is your captain,
once again taking you
under my wing...

40:13.340 --> 40:15.968
by keeping you close
to my heart,
which is where you belong.

40:16.042 --> 40:18.374
This is Crane. Over.
What's going on?

40:18.945 --> 40:20.469
[imitating foreign accent]
Hello, Wilbur.

40:20.613 --> 40:22.342
Wilbur? Who is this?

40:22.982 --> 40:25.109
So you are looking
for the A-Team?

40:25.185 --> 40:27.153
You're out of luck, Wilbur!

40:27.220 --> 40:29.154
The A-Team?
What about the A-Team?

40:31.324 --> 40:32.985
Colonel.
Captain?

40:33.593 --> 40:35.060
The A-Team has escaped.

40:35.128 --> 40:36.288
Escaped?
Yes, sir.

40:36.363 --> 40:38.263
How? Who's responsible?

40:40.400 --> 40:42.960
But l know
how Smith thinks, Captain.

40:43.036 --> 40:46.335
He won't leave this area
till his business
with Kid Harmon is finished.

40:46.406 --> 40:48.874
You can count on it.
Let's move out.

40:57.317 --> 40:59.478
(announcer on PA)
Katz in 01 is all over
Kid Harmon...

40:59.552 --> 41:01.076
down the back straight.

41:09.929 --> 41:13.797
Jones in the 16 car
is smoking under-braking
into the turns.

41:13.867 --> 41:15.926
He could be looking at
a black flag soon.

41:16.069 --> 41:18.162
How's it going, Jack?
Yeah, well....

41:18.638 --> 41:20.868
John?
What are you doing here?
We'll talk later.

41:20.940 --> 41:22.999
But Colonel Decker
will be here
looking for you.

41:23.076 --> 41:24.134
Hmm.

41:25.044 --> 41:27.035
l'd be disappointed
if he wasn't.

41:29.416 --> 41:31.611
That's one of Ludwig's men
over there.

41:31.718 --> 41:33.515
We're in position,
Colonel.

41:33.586 --> 41:35.451
Okay, good.

41:35.522 --> 41:38.616
Number 16 is throwing
a little smoke now.

41:39.559 --> 41:42.027
You guys be sure
our boy gets a fair race.

41:42.095 --> 41:43.187
Okay.

41:46.966 --> 41:51.198
[engine roaring]

41:51.271 --> 41:54.968
[shouting over noise]
Jones, Jones,
you got a telephone call!

41:55.041 --> 41:57.100
Dwight Eisenhower
on line 4.
What?

41:57.177 --> 41:59.145
Your sister
had her kidneys....

41:59.245 --> 42:00.337
[talking gibberish]

42:00.413 --> 42:01.846
What about my sister?
lt dropped!

42:06.986 --> 42:09.580
l sure hope
his sister's kidney turns out
all right. Poor thing.

42:09.656 --> 42:13.023
We're gonna have to remember
to send her a get-well card.
What do you think?

42:13.293 --> 42:14.783
You don't think
anything.

42:21.034 --> 42:22.126
Hey, who the heck
are you?

42:22.202 --> 42:24.397
Don't worry about anything.
Jones had an emergency.

42:24.471 --> 42:28.066
This is his twin brother.
Don't you say anything,
don't you say one thing.

42:34.781 --> 42:37.875
Jones at number 16 is
back in the competition.

42:37.951 --> 42:40.943
Attaboy, B.A.,
attaboy. Get on it now.

42:41.020 --> 42:42.954
(Face on radio)
All right, 01,
you want to get 01...

42:43.022 --> 42:44.114
he's right ahead of you.
There you go.

42:47.260 --> 42:49.251
Dad, they're trying
to run him off the track.

42:49.329 --> 42:51.729
l know it.
(Hannibal)
Now, Dana, relax.

42:51.798 --> 42:53.823
We got a little plan.

42:53.900 --> 42:55.492
Okay, B.A.

42:55.568 --> 42:58.935
Give that powder puff
a little jolt of adrenalin.

42:59.205 --> 43:00.331
You got it.

43:13.753 --> 43:16.881
(announcer on PA)
Katz in 01 is cartwheeling
through the infield.

43:21.361 --> 43:23.295
Attaboy, B.A., attaboy.
Way to go.

43:26.232 --> 43:30.999
Katz is out of the car.
He's shaken, but walking
under his own power..

43:31.070 --> 43:32.935
All right, now take care
of the other slime balls.

43:33.006 --> 43:33.995
(B.A.)
I'm on it.

43:34.073 --> 43:36.098
Uh-oh. Better
hurry it up, Hannibal.

43:36.175 --> 43:37.972
Looks like Decker's got
a surprise party for us.

43:45.151 --> 43:46.709
Well, things are
getting interesting.

43:46.786 --> 43:48.014
(Jack)
You gotta get out of here.

43:48.087 --> 43:50.055
He's going to come
and pick you up
and you know that.

43:50.123 --> 43:51.613
Relax, Jack,
we got plenty of time.

43:51.691 --> 43:54.159
Enjoy the end of the race.
Here they come.

43:54.227 --> 43:58.596
lf the A-Team's inside
these walls,
they'd better not escape.

43:59.032 --> 44:00.522
You two,
take those bleachers...

44:00.600 --> 44:02.795
Captain, take the men
and look those bleachers over.

44:02.869 --> 44:04.131
Disperse!

44:20.119 --> 44:23.020
(announcer on PA)
The 16 car's up
on Szollosi in 95.

44:23.089 --> 44:24.647
It's getting mean out there.

44:30.430 --> 44:32.295
16 and 95 touch.

44:59.759 --> 45:01.556
The Kid has closed on Ludwig.

45:22.181 --> 45:25.275
He's alongside.
He's nosing him
on the inside...

45:25.351 --> 45:27.615
and he triumphs at the flag.

45:29.856 --> 45:30.914
[all cheering]

45:30.990 --> 45:32.958
All right!
All right!

45:35.895 --> 45:37.123
Come on.

45:37.563 --> 45:38.791
Come on!

45:38.898 --> 45:42.800
[crowd cheering]

45:57.316 --> 45:59.910
You win nothing.
You get out of my way,
old man.

45:59.986 --> 46:00.975
[groans]

46:03.156 --> 46:05.181
l should have done that
a long time ago.

46:10.063 --> 46:11.428
What a happy day, huh?

46:23.476 --> 46:24.602
[tires screeching]
There they go!

46:38.324 --> 46:41.191
l love it when a plan
comes together.

46:52.972 --> 46:54.633
[all cheering]
All right!
Check it out!

46:54.807 --> 46:55.933
[cheering]

46:56.175 --> 46:58.871
Can you believe it?
lsn't this the biggest thing
you've ever seen?

46:58.945 --> 47:00.742
(Hannibal)
lndeed.
lt is great, man.

47:00.813 --> 47:04.146
Well, we'll just have
to build an addition to
the house just to keep it in.

47:04.217 --> 47:06.014
We'll have to build
that addition
to the house...

47:06.085 --> 47:07.313
just to put
all our kids in.

47:07.386 --> 47:10.878
Let me get through
this one first, okay?
Okay.

47:10.957 --> 47:13.187
Uncle John, l don't know
how we can thank you enough...

47:13.259 --> 47:17.093
for all that you, and Face,
B.A., and Murdock did.

47:17.163 --> 47:18.824
Oh, it's nothing, Dana.

47:18.898 --> 47:20.490
You know, the thing
l don't understand...

47:20.566 --> 47:23.228
is how did Colonel Decker
ever find out
that you were here?

47:23.536 --> 47:24.662
Oh, well...

47:24.737 --> 47:27.968
Decker may be obnoxious,
but he's very determined.

47:28.641 --> 47:32.475
Listen, son, there's something
you ought to know about that.

47:32.545 --> 47:35.070
Yes, your father
promised me...

47:35.148 --> 47:37.673
that he would personally
ask around quietly...

47:37.750 --> 47:41.208
and find out exactly
what happened,
like the good friend he is.

47:43.689 --> 47:45.680
And a good friend
l'll always be.

47:53.866 --> 47:56.027
Well, we better
get going, huh?

47:56.102 --> 47:59.868
[in ltalian accent]
Si, si. We hate to go but
we got to fly back to Rome...

47:59.939 --> 48:04.706
where our families
are awaiting
the traditional grape harvest.

48:04.911 --> 48:07.402
That's right, Murdock.
You remember?

48:07.814 --> 48:09.247
And we don't wanna be late.

48:09.315 --> 48:12.045
And l especially like
the part where we get
to stomp the grapes.

48:12.118 --> 48:14.814
And we keep on stomping them,
all day long.

48:14.887 --> 48:16.752
(Murdock)
You don't have
to get so riled up!

48:16.823 --> 48:19.053
Stomp! Stomp! Stomp!

